ldman Sachs resurgence. After a first quarter that delighted Wall Street an=
alysts, the firm=E2=80=99s stock is at or near its all-time high, and the c=
horus of <b>David Solomon </b>doubters has gone quiet. I chatted with <b>Jo=
hn Waldron</b>, Solomon=E2=80=99s second-in-command, about the mood in and =
around the bank=E2=80=94and how, exactly, Goldman got back to being <i>Gold=
man</i>. <br/><br/><i>But first=E2=80=A6</i><br/></p>
